external_knowledge:
- Kickoff return refers to a play where a player catches a ball that was kicked by the opposing team and tries to run it back as far as possible towards the opposing team's end zone.; 
- Top kickoff return performance refers to the player's best return in terms of yards gained.; 
- Team information includes the team name and the name and location of their stadium.; 
- Season details include the year, start date, end date, and the number of teams that appeared in the Super Bowl, conference championships, division championships, and playoffs during that season.
